The paper discusses counterfactual explanations, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on making these explanations more interpretable and attainable for humans, which suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the importance of counterfactual faithfulness, which relates to the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Ethics). The use of manifold learning techniques suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision), while the focus on user empowerment suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
